a and racism, problematic national security practices, inimical politicians, and other troubling warning signs. Yet, despite these challenges, these diverse communities continue to display remarkable resilience. An open-minded and substantive reflection on the day-to-day realities for Muslim communities, Protecting Multiculturalism seeks a way forward for the Canadian multicultural experiment - a future that is marked by dignity and diversity in an increasingly fraught era.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aMulticulturalismzCanada. 0aMuslimsxCultural assimilationzCanada. 0aMuslimsxRehabilitationzCanada. 0aNational securityzCanada. 0aRacismzCanada. 0aSocial integrationzCanada. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / World / Canadian.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077355416040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773554160423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773554160/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles